{
    "id": "electronics/arduino-blink",
    "title": "Blink an LED with Arduino",
    "description": "Learn to program a microcontroller by blinking an LED.",
    "image": "/assets/quests/electronics_arduino_blink_led.jpg",
    "npc": "/assets/npc/orion.jpg",
    "start": "start",
    "dialogue": [
        {
            "id": "start",
            "text": "Orion here. Ready to blink an LED with a microcontroller? Dry surface, discharge static, goggles on, and keep the USB cable unplugged until wiring is checked.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "materials",
                    "text": "Absolutely! What do I need?"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "materials",
            "text": "Gather an Arduino Uno, Breadboard, two Jumper Wires, a 220 Ω resistor, a 5 mm LED, safety goggles, a USB Type-A to Type-B cable, a laptop with the Arduino IDE, and a resistor color chart. If the IDE isn't installed, run the install process. Confirm red-red-brown (220 Ω). Wire the LED to pin 13 through the resistor and the short leg to GND. Keep power unplugged while wiring.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "process",
                    "process": "arduino-ide-install",
                    "text": "Install the Arduino IDE"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "upload",
                    "text": "Got it all wired up. What's next?",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "72b4448e-27d9-4746-bd3a-967ff13f501b",
                            "count": 1
                        },
